        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:57AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 257 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
northwest of Echo, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Charleston...                     Milltown...
Branch...                         Washburn...
Burnville...                      Crossroads...
Witcherville...                   Fort Chaffee...
Dayton...                         Mansfield...
Greenwood...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
